text: Mick Lynch (12 May 1878 – 14 June 1944) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood in the Victorian Football League (VFL). In 1899 he was cleared to Richmond but he never played a senior game for them. == Notes == == External links == * *Mick Lynch's profile at Collingwood Forever Category:1878 births Category:1944 deaths Category:Australian rules footballers from Victoria (Australia) Category:Collingwood Football Club players
